<br>
This would be true IF I DIDNT TELL THEM 50 TIMES where it is. Geez. How difficult is &quot; The white sticker on the back of the tower&quot;. Golly, thats hard. And if they cannot find it ( maybe the sticker is gone or soemthing, whatever) then just know WHAT KIND of computer you have. This isn't freaking rocket science. If a person calls in, and says &quot;My thingie is broken&quot; and refuses to say even what kind of computer they have, whats broken, whats not working, anything, do not even know if its a desktop ( aka personal computer that sits on a desk) or a laptop ( the small notebook kind that can sit on your lap)and then get mad when we can't help, it makes me want to pull my hair out. If you are that fucking stupid then have someone else who knows how to work at least a toothbrush call. Sad part is...the MAJORITY of people who call me are IT managers. Today, when speaking with one, after he couldn't find the service tag, I asked what kind of server he has. Expecting to hear &quot;Poweredge whatever&quot;, once again, I was completely floored, when he said &quot;Winxp&quot;. <br>
<br>
I am not saying all people who call tech support are stupid, and it is understandable that they dont know how to fix what is wrong, It is also understandable that they may not be able to find this tag, but there are limits to my patience. If you cant even read the words &quot;Optiplex&quot; or whatever else, thats ON THE BOX, can't even say WHAT is wrong or why you are calling, then for the love of god, have soemone else call. And when I explain to the caller for the 10th time that ~I~ Am not a tech, so could not help them at all, that my job is to transfer calls, don't say &quot;It's just a simple question&quot;. and proceed to tell me a 15 minute story, at the end of which, I just transfer you like I said I was going to do. Additionally, lots of these people CAN and do find the service tag, but sit there for 10 minutes trying to convince me that I need the reference/case number instead, even when I explain that I cannot help them with that number, to give the TECHNICIAN that number, which I will be glad to transfer them to as soon as I know what kind of  computer they have, and then they get mad at me and say FINE  take the stupid service tag if you are gonna be picky about it. <br>
<br>
It boggles my mind, that if these people would just shut the hell up for 5 seconds and answer my questions, even if it's with I dont know, ( to an extent) their wait time in the queue would be tons less. More time they spend whining at me, is more callers that get in ahead of them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skylias>Skylias</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/co/snowboarding98/mah_ranjah.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tribulation Officer<br>
